org.opends.sdk.schema
Class SchemaLocal<T>

java.lang.Object
  org.opends.sdk.schema.SchemaLocal<T>
Type Parameters:
T - The type of the schema-local variable.
public class SchemaLocal<T>
extends Object

This class provides schema-local variables. These variables differ from their normal counterparts in that each schema has its own independently initialized copy of the variable. SchemaLocal instances are typically private static fields in classes that wish to associate state with a schema (e.g., a schema dependent cache).

get

public final T get(Schema schema)
Returns the value in the provided schema's copy of this schema-local variable. If the variable has no value associated with the schema, it is first initialized to the value returned by an invocation of the initialValue() method.

Parameters:
schema - The schema whose copy of the schema-local variable is being requested.
Returns:
The schema-local value.

remove

public final void remove(Schema schema)
Removes the provided schema's value for this schema-local variable. If this schema-local variable is subsequently read, its value will be reinitialized by invoking its initialValue() method, unless its value is set in the interim. This may result in multiple invocations of the initialValue() method.

Parameters:
schema - The schema whose copy of the schema-local variable is being removed.

initialValue

protected T initialValue()
Returns the provided schema's "initial value" for this schema-local variable. This method will be invoked the first time the variable is accessed with the get(org.opends.sdk.schema.Schema) method for each schema, unless the set(org.opends.sdk.schema.Schema, T) method has been previously invoked, in which case the initialValue() method will not be invoked.

Normally, this method is invoked at most once per schema, but it may be invoked again in case of subsequent invocations of remove(org.opends.sdk.schema.Schema) followed by get(org.opends.sdk.schema.Schema). This implementation simply returns null; if the programmer desires schema-local variables to have an initial value other than null, SchemaLocal must be subclassed, and this method overridden. Typically, an anonymous inner class will be used.

Returns:
The initial value for this schema-local.
